  "lore": "The Gorgon pattern of Tactical Dreadnought Armour was one of a number of on-going attempts by Ferrus Manus and his cadre of Iron Fathers to ref ne and augment the various patterns of Terminator armour employed by the Legiones Astartes forces, though by the time of the Primarch’s death, a full issue to his Legion was never approved. One of the most extreme technological examples of the Iron Hands’ innovation, this prototype required bonding to its wearer. In battle this ensured superior mobility and reaction speed, without sacrificing resilience.",
